acceptance_criteria: "ADR records the decision for: (1) persistent read-index format + invalidation, (2) item-directory fan-out scheme + format_version migration path, (3) bounded-output/cursor-pagination contract, (4) claim/lock scaling approach, (5) git-repo growth policy (packing, history compaction cadence); status accepted (item closed) before dependent implementation tasks start"
goal: project management = context management
objective: Fix the architectural rules that let pm stay sub-second and bounded-token as workspaces grow to 100k-1M items with thousands of concurrent agents
value: "Without a scale strategy decided up front, index/sharding/pagination work would be ad-hoc and could require repeated storage migrations"
why_now: Product goal explicitly targets workspaces of hundreds of thousands to millions of items with thousands of parallel agents; current read paths scan the full item directory and output is unbounded by default
